    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Ash Wednesday)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "Almighty and everlasting God, you hate nothing you have made and forgive the sins of all who are penitent: Create and make in us new and contrite hearts, that we, worthily lamenting our sins and acknowledging our wretchedness, may obtain of you, the God of all mercy, perfect remission and forgiveness; through Jesus Christ our Lord, who lives and reigns with you and the Holy Spirit, one God, for ever and ever. Amen.",
    "section": "Ash Wednesday",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": null,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Ash Wednesday",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": null,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "rubric_ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "name": "Rubric (Ash Wednesday)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "rubric",
    "body_text": "After the Sermon, all stand, and the Celebrant or Minister appointed invites the people to the observance of a holy Lent, saying",
    "section": "Ash Wednesday",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": null,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Ash Wednesday",
      "kind": "rubric",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": null,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Ash Wednesday)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "Dear People of God: The first Christians observed with great devotion the days of our Lord's passion and resurrection, and it became the custom of the Church to prepare for them by a",
    "section": "Ash Wednesday",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": null,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Ash Wednesday",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": null,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Ash Wednesday)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "season of penitence and fasting. This season of Lent provided a time in which converts to the faith were prepared for Holy Baptism. It was also a time when those who, because of notorious sins, had been separated from the body of the faithful were reconciled by penitence and forgiveness, and restored to the fellowship of the Church. Thereby, the whole congregation was put in mind of the message of pardon and absolution set forth in the Gospel of our Savior, and of the need which all Christians continually have to renew their repentance and faith. I invite you, therefore, in the name of the Church, to the observance of a holy Lent, by self-examination and repentance; by prayer, fasting, and self-denial; and by reading and meditating on God's holy Word. And, to make a right beginning of repentance, and as a mark of our mortal nature, let us now kneel before the Lord, our maker and redeemer.",
    "section": "Ash Wednesday",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 264,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Ash Wednesday",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 264,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "rubric_ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "name": "Rubric (Ash Wednesday)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "rubric",
    "body_text": "Silence is then kept for a time, all kneeling.",
    "section": "Ash Wednesday",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 264,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Ash Wednesday",
      "kind": "rubric",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 264,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "optional_block_ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "name": "Optional Block (Ash Wednesday)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "If ashes are to be imposed, the Celebrant says the following prayer Almighty God, you have created us out of the dust of the earth: Grant that these ashes may be to us a sign of our mortality and penitence, that we may remember that it is only by your gracious gift that we are given everlasting life; through Jesus Christ our Savior. Amen. The ashes are imposed with the following words Remember that you are dust, and to dust you shall return.",
    "section": "Ash Wednesday",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 264,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Ash Wednesday",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 264,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": true
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "rubric_ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "name": "Rubric (Ash Wednesday)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "rubric",
    "body_text": "The following Psalm is then sung or said",
    "section": "Ash Wednesday",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 264,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Ash Wednesday",
      "kind": "rubric",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 264,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "psalm_51_verse_1_anglican",
    "name": "Psalm 51 verse 1",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "psalm-verse",
    "body_text": "Have mercy on me, O God, according to your\nloving-kindness; *\nin your great compassion blot out my offenses.",
    "section": "Ash Wednesday",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 265,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Ash Wednesday",
      "kind": "psalm-verse",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 265,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": 51,
      "verse_number": 1,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "psalm_51_verse_2_anglican",
    "name": "Psalm 51 verse 2",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "psalm-verse",
    "body_text": "Wash me through and through from my wickedness *\nand cleanse me from my sin.",
    "section": "Ash Wednesday",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 265,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Ash Wednesday",
      "kind": "psalm-verse",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 265,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": 51,
      "verse_number": 2,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
