  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "Most holy and merciful Father: We confess to you and to one another, and to the whole communion of saints in heaven and on earth, that we have sinned by our own fault in thought, word, and deed; by what we have done, and by what we have left undone.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 266,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 266,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "rubric_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Rubric (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "rubric",
    "body_text": "The Celebrant continues",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 266,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "rubric",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 266,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "We have not loved you with our whole heart, and mind, and strength. We have not loved our neighbors as ourselves. We have not forgiven others, as we have been forgiven. Have mercy on us, Lord.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 266,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 266,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "We have been deaf to your call to serve, as Christ served us. We have not been true to the mind of Christ. We have grieved your Holy Spirit. Have mercy on us, Lord.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 266,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 266,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "We confess to you, Lord, all our past unfaithfulness: the pride, hypocrisy, and impatience of our lives, We confess to you, Lord.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 267,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 267,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "Our self-indulgent appetites and ways, and our exploitation of other people, We confess to you, Lord.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 267,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 267,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "Our anger at our own frustration, and our envy of those more fortunate than ourselves, We confess to you, Lord.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 267,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 267,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "Our intemperate love of worldly goods and comforts, and our dishonesty in daily life and work, We confess to you, Lord.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 267,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 267,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "Our negligence in prayer and worship, and our failure to commend the faith that is in us, We confess to you, Lord.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 267,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 267,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "Accept our repentance, Lord, for the wrongs we have done: for our blindness to human need and suffering, and our indifference to injustice and cruelty, Accept our repentance, Lord.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 267,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 267,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "For all false judgments, for uncharitable thoughts toward our neighbors, and for our prejudice and contempt toward those who differ from us, Accept our repentance, Lord.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 267,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 267,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "For our waste and pollution of your creation, and our lack of concern for those who come after us, Accept our repentance, Lord.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 267,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 267,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "Restore us, good Lord, and let your anger depart from us; Favorably hear us, for your mercy is great.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 267,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 267,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "Accomplish in us the work of your salvation, That we may show forth your glory in the world.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 267,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 267,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "By the cross and passion of your Son our Lord, Bring us with all your saints to the joy of his resurrection.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 268,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 268,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "rubric_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Rubric (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "rubric",
    "body_text": "The Bishop, if present, or the Priest, stands and, facing the people, says",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 268,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "rubric",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 268,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Text (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "Almighty God, the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who desires not the death of sinners, but rather that they may turn from their wickedness and live, has given power and commandment to his ministers to declare and pronounce to his people, being penitent, the absolution and remission of their sins. He pardons and absolves all those who truly repent, and with sincere hearts believe his holy Gospel. Therefore we beseech him to grant us true repentance and his Holy Spirit, that those things may please him which we do on this day, and that the rest of our life hereafter may be pure and holy, so that at the last we may come to his eternal joy; through Jesus Christ our Lord. Amen.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 268,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
      "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
      "section": "Litany of Penitence",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "ashwed.html",
      "page_number": 268,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "rubric_litany_of_penitence_anglican",
    "name": "Rubric (Litany of Penitence)",
    "liturgy_name": "Ash Wednesday",
    "liturgy_slug": "ash_wednesday_anglican",
    "kind": "rubric",
    "body_text": "A deacon or lay reader leading the service remains kneeling and substitutes the prayer for forgiveness appointed at Morning Prayer. The Peace is then exchanged. In the absence of a bishop or priest, all that precedes may be led by a deacon or lay reader. The Litany of Penitence may be used at other times, and may be preceded by an appropriate invitation and a penitential psalm. When Communion follows, the service continues with the Offertory.",
    "section": "Litany of Penitence",
    "source_file": "ashwed.html",
    "page_number": 268,
